BLUEPRINT
Official MCP

Tailwind Plus is a collection of professionally designed, pre-built UI components built with Tailwind CSS. It's a commercial product, offering a range of application layouts, marketing sections, and component examples. However, some components are only available for React and Vue.

Consider Tailwind Plus when you need high-quality, visually appealing UI components and have a project built with React or Vue (for some components). It's suitable for projects where you want to save time on design and front-end development by using pre-made components.

Avoid Tailwind Plus if you're working on a project with a different framework other than React or Vue, or if you require extensive customization beyond what the components offer. Also, if you prefer open-source solutions or have a limited budget, Tailwind Plus might not be the right choice due to its paid license.
Some components are only available for React and Vue only, some don't need JS and can be used with any framework

Tailwind Plus has 93 Components, 31 of them are unique â€“ for example pagination and button group are considered as same. However, Tailwind Plus has many variations of the same component, and has Templates which are not included in the component count.
Tailwind Plus has light and dark themes
Does not support more than 2 themes at the same time
Imported JavaScript bundle size (minified) for Headless UI which is required for Tailwind Plus

Tailwind Plus requires Headless UI which has 21 third-party dependencies for Vue version and 25 third-party dependencies for React version. Using more third-party dependencies increases the risk of security vulnerabilities, compatibility problems, and long-term maintenance headaches from deprecated packages.
Tailwind Plus requires Headless UI which has 11MB to 16MB of dependencies for Vue version and React version respectively.
Tailwind Plus does not use semantic CSS class names. Using semantic and descriptive CSS class names improves readability and maintainability of code independent of the current framework.
Tailwind Plus requires changing class names one by one at build time to do any customization
Many components require React or Vue, which requires a Node.js environment
Tailwind Plus does not provide micro CSS files for each component
Tailwind Plus uses wide-gamut P3 colors by default
Tailwind Plus does not support right-to-left (RTL) layouts
Tailwind Plus customizations requires changing Tailwind CSS class names at build time
Tailwind Plus doesn not use native CSS nesting

Chakra UI is a React component library that provides a set of accessible and reusable UI components for building modern web applications. It offers a range of customizable elements and tools designed to promote best practices for accessibility and developer experience.

Use Chakra UI when you're building React applications and want to prioritize accessibility and developer experience. It's suitable for projects that benefit from a consistent design system and a focus on building inclusive user interfaces.

Avoid Chakra UI if you're not using React, or if you need a design that significantly deviates from the default Chakra UI styles. Also, consider the dependency size and the potential impact on your application's performance.
Chakra UI works only with React
Chakra UI has 59 Components, 48 of them are unique â€“ for example pagination and button group are considered as same.
Chakra UI has light and dark themes

Chakra UI has 146 third-party dependencies. Using more third-party dependencies increases the risk of security vulnerabilities, compatibility problems, and long-term maintenance headaches from deprecated packages.
Chakra UI CSS file is not available on CDN
Chakra UI does not use semantic CSS class names. Using semantic and descriptive CSS class names improves readability and maintainability of code independent of the current framework.
Chakra UI requires changing JavaScript props one by one at build time to do design token customization
Chakra UI requires a Node.js environment
Chakra UI does not provide micro CSS files for each component
Chakra UI does not use wide-gamut P3 colors by default
Chakra UI does not support right-to-left (RTL) layouts
Chakra UI customizations requires changing JavaScript props at build time
Chakra UI doesn not use native CSS nesting
